Implement `app/api/annotations/[id]/route.ts` as the per-annotation CRUD API route.

Requirements
1. Export `dynamic = "force-dynamic"`.
2. Implement `GET`, `PUT`, and `DELETE` handlers using Next.js App Router dynamic params as `Promise<{ id: string }>`; `await params` in each handler.
3. `GET /api/annotations/[id]`:
   - Read one row from `annotations` by `id`.
   - Return 404 `{ error: "Annotation not found" }` when missing.
   - Return the annotation object directly (not wrapped), mapping DB row fields to `Annotation`:
     `id`, `sectionId`, `timestamp`, `text`, `createdAt`, nullable fields normalized with `?? null`, `analysis` parsed from `row.analysis` JSON string (or `null`), `resolved` converted via `Boolean(row.resolved)`, and `inputMethod` defaulting to `"typed"`.
4. `PUT /api/annotations/[id]`:
   - Return 404 `{ error: "Annotation not found" }` if the record does not exist.
   - Accept partial updates for `text`, `sectionId`, and `timestamp`.
   - If none of those fields are provided, return 400 `{ error: "No fields to update" }`.
   - Update only provided fields, then re-fetch and return the updated annotation using the same mapping as GET.
5. `DELETE /api/annotations/[id]`:
   - Return 404 `{ error: "Annotation not found" }` if the record does not exist.
   - Delete by `id` and return `{ success: true }`.
6. No authentication checks.
7. On any unexpected error in any handler, log with `console.error(...)` and return 500 `{ error: "Internal Server Error" }`.

Dependencies
<lib_db>
<include>video_editor_pdd/lib/db.ts</include>
</lib_db>

Deliverable
- `app/api/annotations/[id]/route.ts`
